snippet.textDisplay: I will be completely honest and UNBIASED. The performance was great because the song in itself is so emotional And beautiful, from an iconic singer. Also, as a father, her dad's reaction is beautiful. That being said, I thought she sounded average. That song, as is the case with so many of Juanga's songs, is incredibly hard to sing. I don't think that deserves all four chairs, I think everyone got caught up in the emotion of the song, which is easy to do. I'll probably get negative responses, but I'm just saying, it was good, average..
